Phase 3 — Catalog foundations
Service: catalog-service · MongoDB `catalog` db

No functional dependency on Phase 1/2 (catalog-service makes no gRPC calls
to identity-service — CAT-006's admin-only write restriction is enforced
the same way as identity's admin endpoints, via Kong's forwarded role
claim). Sequenced after identity so there's already an Administrator token
to test the admin-only endpoint with.

Scenarios covered: 11, 12.

---

## POST /api/products  (admin only)

Scenario 11. CAT-001 (name, description, category, unit price, stock
count required), CAT-002 (unit price > 0), CAT-003 (stock count >= 0,
whole number), CAT-004 (exactly one category), CAT-006 (admin only).

Request:
```json
POST /api/products
Authorization: Bearer <jwt for admin>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Trail Runner 2.0",
  "description": "Lightweight trail running shoe, standard fit.",
  "category": "Footwear",
  "unitPrice": "89.99",
  "stockCount": 25
}
```

Response — 201 Created:
```json
{
  "id": "10000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001",
  "name": "Trail Runner 2.0",
  "description": "Lightweight trail running shoe, standard fit.",
  "category": "Footwear",
  "unitPrice": "89.99",
  "stockCount": 25,
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "createdAt": "2026-07-13T09:30:00Z"
}
```

Response — 400 Bad Request (CAT-002, a zero or negative price):
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "INVALID_PRICE",
    "message": "unitPrice must be greater than zero."
  }
}
```

Response — 403 Forbidden (a Customer calling this — CAT-006):
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "FORBIDDEN",
    "message": "Only an Administrator can create a product."
  }
}
```

