## GET /api/products

Scenario 12. CAT-006 (Customers/public can browse and search), CAT-007
(zero stock is still shown, marked out of stock), CAT-008 (Deactivated
products are fully excluded, regardless of stock).

Request:
```json
GET /api/products?category=Footwear
```

Response — 200 OK (prod-0002-style zero-stock item included and flagged;
a Deactivated product like prod-0005 never appears here at all):
```json
{
  "items": [
    {
      "id": "10000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001",
      "name": "Trail Runner 2.0",
      "category": "Footwear",
      "unitPrice": "89.99",
      "inStock": true
    },
    {
      "id": "10000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000004",
      "name": "Trail Runner 2.0",
      "category": "Footwear",
      "unitPrice": "94.99",
      "inStock": true
    }
  ],
  "total": 2
}
```

`inStock` is a derived boolean (`stockCount > 0`), not the raw count — a
customer browsing doesn't need the exact number, only whether it's
orderable right now (CAT-007 says out-of-stock is marked, not that the
count is published).

